ğŸ¯ Objective
Alternate Data Streams (ADS) is a feature of the NTFS file system that allows files to contain hidden data streams in addition to their main content.
Attackers abuse ADS to:
Hide malicious payloads
Store sensitive data covertly
Bypass traditional file inspection

This lab focuses on:
âœ” Detecting hidden NTFS streams
âœ” Extracting concealed data
âœ” Understanding ADS as an anti-forensics technique

