Windows PowerShell (Administrator)
NoVirusThanks Stream Detector

ğŸ“Œ Procedure (Key Steps)
ğŸ–¥ï¸ Part 1 â€” Detecting ADS Using PowerShell
Launch Windows PowerShell as Administrator
Navigate to system directory:
cd C:\Windows\System32
Scan recursively for hidden streams:
gci -recurse | % { gi $_.FullName -stream * } | where stream -ne ':$Data'
â¡ Lists files containing Alternate Data Streams

In real-world attacks, ADS are attached to normal-looking files to evade suspicion.

ğŸ“¤ Part 2 â€” Extracting Hidden ADS Content
To view data stored inside a hidden stream:
get-content -path C:\Windows\System32\file.txt -stream secret_file1.txt
â¡ Displays the concealed data from the ADS stream

ğŸ” Part 3 â€” Detecting ADS Using Stream Detector Tool
Launch NoVirusThanks Stream Detector
Select directory to scan (example: C:\Windows\System32)
Start scan
â¡ Tool lists:
Stream name
